io.protostuff.runtime

Class PolymorphicSchema

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.protostuff.runtime.PolymorphicSchema
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Schema<Object>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ArraySchema, ArraySchemas.Base, ClassSchema, NumberSchema, ObjectSchema, PolymorphicCollectionSchema, PolymorphicEnumSchema, PolymorphicMapSchema, PolymorphicThrowableSchema

    public abstract class PolymorphicSchema
extends Object
implements Schema<Object>
    Used when the type is either polymorphic or too complex. Unlike DerivativeSchema, this is designed to have no concept of merging.
    Author:
    David Yu
    Date created:
    Apr 30, 2012
